cn:association.cn:title: US Treasury yields climb after jobless numbers, stronger industrial production data
cn:association.cn:summary: U.S. government debt yields rose Thursday after jobless claims unexpectedly rose and industrial production beat projections.
cn:association.cn:linkHeadline: US Treasury yields climb after jobless numbers, stronger industrial production data
cn:association.headline: US Treasury yields climb after jobless numbers, stronger industrial production data
cn:association.cn:shorterHeadline: US Treasury yields climb after jobless numbers, stronger industrial production
cn:association.cn:shorterDescription: U.S. government debt yields rose Thursday after jobless claims unexpectedly rose and industrial production beat projections.
cn:association.cn:shortestDescription: U.S. government debt yields rose Thursday after jobless claims rose and industrial production beat forecasts.
cn:association.cn:bodyTeaser:
U.S. government debt yields rose Thursday after jobless claims unexpectedly rose and U.S. industrial production beat Wall Street expectations.

The yield on the benchmark 10-year Treasury note sat higher at around 2.347 percent at 9:49 a.m. ET, while the yield on the 30-year Treasury bond was up at 2.789 percent. Bond yields move inversely to prices.

Meanwhile, the 2-year Treasury note yield hit a high of 1.716 percent its highest level since Oct. 2008 when the 2-year note yielded as high as 1.716.
